  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Now it came to pass, that at what time the chest was brought unto the king's office by the hand of the Levites,.... The place where his officer or officers met, appointed for this service; very probably in one of the chambers of the temple, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and when they saw that there was much money: see 2 Kings 12:10, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and when they saw that there was much money: see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Kings 12:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the king's scribe; or secretary: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the high priest's officer; his \"sagan\", or deputy priest: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "came and emptied the chest; poured out the money, and told it, and put it up in bags, 2 Kings 12:10 and took it, and carried it to its place again, 2 Chronicles 24:8, by the hands of the Levites that brought it: ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "came and emptied the chest; poured out the money, and told it, and put it up in bags, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Kings 12:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " and took it, and carried it to its place again, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 24:8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", by the hands of the Levites that brought it: ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and thus they did day by day; as often as the chest was full, or they perceived there was much in it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and gathered money in abundance; enough to repair the house, ornament it, and furnish it with vessels that were wanting. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and gathered money in abundance; enough to repair the house, ornament it, and furnish it with vessels that were wanting. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "Now it came to pass, that at what time {e} the chest was brought unto the king's office by the hand of the Levites, and when they saw that there was much money, the king's scribe and the high priest's officer came and emptied the chest, and took it, and carried it to his place again. Thus they did day by day, and gathered money in abundance.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Now it came to pass, that at what time ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{e}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " the chest was brought unto the king's office by the hand of the Levites, and when they saw that ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "i",
            "class": "",
            "text": "there was",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " much money, the king's scribe and the high priest's officer came and emptied the chest, and took it, and carried it to his place again. Thus they did day by day, and gathered money in abundance.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(e) Such as were faithful men whom the king had appointed for that matter.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
