  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 11.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Unto the king's office.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Not \"office\" in the modern technical business sense; the meaning is the care, charge, or custody of the king, the Hebrew word being ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "פְקֻדַּת",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; nor does this necessitate the supposition of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "personal",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " care of the king. The body of this verse leaves it quite open to possibility, in harmony with the usage of the Hebrew language and its idiom, that the process described took place, if necessary, more than once in a day, and, on the other hand, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "not",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " necessarily every evening. The change of the number of the verb in \"they emptied,\" etc., and the apparent statement that those who ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "emptied",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "carried back",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the chest, betoken that while ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "the king's",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "scribe",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 4:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "and the high priest's officer",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " stood by, the usual Levite functionaries did the work. The phrase, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "day by day",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", is not necessarily equivalent to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "every evening",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "time after time.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " 2 Chronicles 24:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
